YOUNGSTERS from a city primary school celebrated a cash boost from a travel charity.Glasgow Airport's Flight Path Fund gave &pound;3168 to Bearsden Primary School to help them deliver a lunch activity club.The Enjoyaball club aims to promote exercise and wellbeing during kids' lunch breaks for primaries one to five.Mr Meehan, Head Teacher at BPS said; &quot;The granting of the FlightPath Fund is fantastic news for the pupils of Bearsden Primary School! We are always looking for ways to improve the school experience for our pupils and this funding will help us to provide high quality, structured and fun games during lunch times. Over 240 of our youngest pupils will directly benefit from this funding and I would like to thank the Bearsden Primary Fundraising Group for all of their efforts and the Flight Path Fund for their consideration of our proposal&quot;